<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-1151 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper describes the development of wholly metallic surface-combustionradiant gas burners constructed from a new heat resisting alloy in theform of fine fibres sintered together to produce a rigid yet permeablematerial. Prototype burner constructions covering a range of fibre diameters,porosities and thicknesses have been evaluated to determine the influenceof material properties on performance, including surface temperatureand nitrogen oxide emission.</TEXT></DOC>